{
  "texts": [
    "Then Statements (a)-(c) hold for any K. (3-iv) (Jacobson-Jarden [JJ01, Main Theorem (a)]) Statement (c) holds for any K. (4) (Jarden-Petersen [JP22, Theorem 1.3 (ii)]) Assume that K has characteristic zero and e ≥ 2.",
    "Then for almost all σ ∈ G e K, any finite extension M of K(σ), and any abelian variety A over M, it holds that A(M) div = 0.",
    "The results, including ours, involving the normalized Haar measure are nonconstructive as they are proved by calculating the measures of various subsets in G e K.",
    "Thus they do not give an explicit element for which their statement holds.",
    "Larsen [Lar03] conjectured that the statement on the field K(σ) in (1) holds for any σ ∈ G e K."
  ]
}